One other alternative that I don't see mentioned in Lori's link is that you may find it useful to set multiple remotes (git remote set-url --add <branch_name> <url>), but that assumes your branch name on Bioconductor matches your GitHub.  See stackoverflow.com/a/14290145 (removing the URL prefix to avoid stupid MITM URL rewrites). Then you can have both GitHub Actions and Bioconductor's checks yell at you :o)

